          A Poet&apos;s Guide to Acceptance Testing
        %h3
        %h3
          %a{:href => "#presenter_135"} George Dinwiddie
    %tr
      %td{:colspan => "2"}
        %p The crucial aspect of test automation is creating clear and expressive descriptions of the system being built.  It&rsquo;s easy to write tests that a computer can understand. But can you write tests that people, even non-technical people, can understand?  Will it be obvious whether or not the test is correct?  This is not a matter of dumbing things down.
        %p Highlight the concepts. Express just the right details. There is a synergy between the expressiveness of tests and the maintainability.
        %p
